Over 100 motorcyclists have reportedly attacked Same Global Estate in the Lokogoma area of the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja over the death of their two colleagues. DAILY POST gathered that trouble began in the area on Sunday, when a motorist hit the Okda riders and ran into the estate for safety. The attack, according to an eyewitness, was aimed at apprehending the motorcyclists who was trying to escape being lynched. A police source told DAILY POST that the FCT command has taken over the area to enforce peace. The commandâ€™s spokesperson, Josephine Adeh, could not be reached for comment as of press time.